Justice Joe Acha, Chief Judge, Edo State has urged members of the public to live selflessly for one another. Justice Acha made the call in his address at the valedictory court session in honor of the late justice James Sadoh in Benin. Acha, represented by the number two judge in the state, Justice Iyobosa Okungbowa,  eulogized the life and times of the former jurist whose chamber has produced three senior advocates of Nigeria and two former Nigeria Bar Association presidents. -Advertisement- The two past NBA presidents are Prince Adelanke Odogiyon (SAN),  and Mr Austin Alegeh(SAN) as well as Fedinard Orbih  SAN who the late Sadoh nurtured. According to him, late Justice Sadoh had lived sacrificially in humility, love for others, the community, and ultimately to the Almighty God. In his remark, Edo state Attorney General and Commissioner for Justice, Mr. Oluwole Iyamu represented by the director, public prosecution, Mr. Kingsley Odabi, said the late Sadoh who was the former Bendel state Attorney General and commissioner for justice, was a diligent civil servant who left his foot prints in the state judiciary. On his part, the chairman, of the NBA Benin branch, Mr. Pius Oiwoh said Late justice Sadoh who was a former chairman of the Benin branch of the NBA  had a key eye for young budding talents in the judiciary whom he caught, nurtured, and groomed to greatness. The widow of the late jurist, Mrs. Maria Sadoh told newsmen after the session that she misses her husband as she now has to make all the decisions without him around. POLL Present at the valedictory court session was the Edo state deputy governor, Mr. Philip Shaibu,  principal officers of the judiciary, senior advocates, family members, and other judicial officers of the Edo state judiciary. Late Justice Sadoh was called to Bar on June 23, 1964,  appointed as High court Judge in February 1989, and died at the age of 86.